Enum ReadAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ReadAccess>
      • com.ibm.eznosql.options.ReadAccess
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ReadAccess>
    public enum ReadAccess
extends java.lang.Enum<ReadAccess>
    The ReadAccess enum represents access levels when defining a new Connection instance in Connection.fromDataSetName(String, EnumSet, ConnectionIntegrity, short, boolean). Unless specified, the default is read write access in ascending sequential order.

    A ReadAccess EnumSet can be constructed by specifying none (default) or multiple flag combinations. The following example demonstrates how to initialize an EnumSet with default or multiple flags:

    EnumSet<ReadAccess> flags = EnumSet.noneOf(ReadAccess.class)
    EnumSet<ReadAccess> flags = EnumSet.of(ReadAccess.READ_ONLY, ReadAccess.DESCENDING_KEYS);

    • Enum Constant Summary

      DESCENDING_KEYS
      Indicates descending sequential access when retrieving documents through the primary index.
      FORCE_UPDATE
      Indicates write force is used when attempting to insert a document with a duplicate key name either for the primary index or a unique secondary index.
      READ_ONLY
      Indicates read only access is requested for the connection.
